com.example.link.appfuzzer.XMLdumper

Class XMLdumper

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.link.appfuzzer.XMLdumper.XMLdumper

  • public class XMLdumper
extends java.lang.Object

    Takes care of writing the log files. Log files are created in /data/data/com.example.link.appfuzzer/files/ and are named [package_name][current_set]. There is one log file for each set.

    The workflow for using this class is:

    1. Call startFile(File) with your desired file to write to. This will initialize the file.
    2. Set properties using the various setter methods.
    3. Call writeEvent(). This will write your set properties to the file and reinitialize them.
    4. Call endFile(). This closes the file.

    It is possible to call startFile(File) when a file is already being processed and endFile() when a file is already closed. The methods will print warnings and quit.
